{
  "stem": "27390.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Coming back to the synagogues, as I said before, the-- the-- the three synagogues were the-- the most elaborate synagogues that one can imagine.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They contained large libraries of very-- manuscripts, valuable manuscripts of different Talmudic learning.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And one of the synagogues had two ladies' galleries-- two or three ladies' galleries.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It could hold 1,500-- downstairs it had 1,500 seats.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was a very large synagogue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was called the Old-- the Old Town Synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then there was the Vilna Shul that was the synagogue that was near us that was also a very large synagogue.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then there was a modern, more modern synagogue, which was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] founded by enlightened Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had already an organ in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a mixed choir.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Something like the reform here, in England today.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were the three largest synagogues.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Lodz, as I said, was mainly Orthodox but most of the shops were closed on Shabbat, most of the Jewish shops, I'm talking about.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Before the war, last years before the war broke out, some of the Jews started opening the shops on the Shabbat and the Hasidim used to stand outside the shops and stop the customers from going in and out of the shops.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there were a lot of-- and the-- the shop keepers used to call the police to intervene.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They should move away these Hasidim So there was a lot of tension going.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But on-- mainly, also the-- mainly the shops were-- the food shops I'm talking about, the kosher shops-- most of the things that were sold were kosher.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
